                                <a href="#" class="accordion-title coaching-accordion-section font-bold accordionBtn">How long are EHE exams?</a>
                                <div class="accordion-content" data-tab-content >
                                    <p>It depends on your age and the specific screenings you need. Most patients under age 40 finish their exam in about two hours. Patients over 40 may take between three and four hours to complete their exam, based on any additional screenings ordered by their physician &mdash; such as mammograms or stress test.</p>
